reviews.review_text: Senn 441 aw yeah! I have been listening to all of these 441 tapes of the BCT 84 run, great recordings. The shows are all interesting. El Paso is pretty hilarious. Am I supposed to dock a star for that? Hahaha nope. Help>Slip has a few blips mainly due to its speed and Franklin's doesn't come alive until the end but WOW the Wharf Rat>Gimme is incredible. The first Gimme Some Lovin is a mess but at this point WHO CARES....a bust out led by Phil? More please! A strong space leads to a beautifully developed Playin Reprise and then full blast Bertha>Good Lovin. Casey Jones makes sense to end it, a night full of surprises and a delightful mix of inspired and flubby playing that must have made for a ridiculously awesome East Bay dance party.
